According to Moseley's law, the frequency $
u$ of the emitted X-ray is related to the atomic number $Z$ by the equation:<br><br>$\sqrt{
u} = a(Z - b)$<br><br>where $a$ is a proportionality constant and $b$ is the screening constant.<br><br>For $K_ eta$ radiation, the transition occurs from the M shell ($n=3$) to the K shell ($n=1$). The screening constant $b$ for the K-series is a positive value.<br><br>The equation represents a straight line when $\sqrt{
u}$ is plotted against $Z$.<br><br>At the $Z$-intercept, $\sqrt{
u} = 0$, which gives $Z = b$.<br><br>Since $b > 0$, the graph is a straight line with a positive $Z$-intercept.
